[Circovirus is an emerging disease in dogs and possibly cats. Currently there is not much known about it in dogs, and less about it in cats, if it does affect them. How many tests have come back positive on cats? Or, conversely, how many circovirus tests are negative on these cats?

Outbreaks in California and Ohio previously thought to be circovirus in dogs have proven not to be the case. This vet indicates most of the suspected cases in her area are also negative for the virus. It may prove that cats are not susceptible either.

Michigan may be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/2_1t. - Mod.TG]
